##input

Is used by `<input type="text">` tag , extends [form-element](#form-element) styles with small modifications

since
: 1.0.0

extend
: <%= link_to '%input', '/documentation/include-extend' %>

<% example_html do %>
<div class="container-20em">
  <p>
    <input class="input" name="simple-input">
  </p>
  <p>
    <input class="input" name="disabled-input" disabled
     value="disabled">
  </p>
  <p>
    <input class="input" id="readonly-input" name="readonly-input"
     readonly value="readonly">
  </p>
  <p>
    <input class="input" id="country" name="country"
     placeholder="Country" required>
  </p>
</div>
<% end %>


##textarea

Is used by `<textarea>` tag, extends [input](#input) styles with small modifications

since
: 1.0.0

extend
: <%= link_to '%textarea', '/documentation/include-extend' %>

<% example_html do %>
<div class="container-20em">
  <p>
    <textarea class="textarea" name="simple-textarea"></textarea>
  </p>
  <p>
    <textarea class="textarea no-resize" name="no-resize-textarea"
     placeholder="without resize in firefox, chrome and safari"></textarea>
  </p>
  <p>
    <textarea class="textarea" name="rows-textarea" rows="6"></textarea>
  </p>
</div>
<% end %>


