##label

Is used by `<label>` tag

since
: 1.0.0

extend
: <%= link_to '%label', '/documentation/include-extend' %>

<% example_html do %>
<div class="container-20em">
  <p>
    <label class="label">Without for</label>
    <input class="input">
  </p>
  <p>
    <label class="label" for="description">Description</label>
    <textarea class="input" id="description" name="description"></textarea>
  </p>
  <p>
    <label class="label is-required" for="brand">Brand</label>
    <input class="input" id="brand" name="brand" required>
  </p>
</div>
<% end %>


##checkbox

Is used by `<input type="checkbox">` tag , extends [form-checks](#form-checks) styles with small modifications

since
: 1.0.0

extend
: <%= link_to '%checkbox', '/documentation/include-extend' %>

<% example_html do %>
<div class="container-20em">
  <p>
    <label class="checkbox">
      <input type="checkbox" name="i1">
      Inline 1
    </label>
    <label class="checkbox" name="i2">
      <input type="checkbox">
      Inline 2
    </label>
    <label class="checkbox" name="i3">
      <input type="checkbox">
      Inline 3
    </label>
  </p>
  <p>
    <div>
      <label class="checkbox">
        <input type="checkbox" name="b1">
        Block
      </label>
    </div>
    <div>
      <label class="checkbox" disabled>
        <input type="checkbox" name="b2" disabled>
        Block disabled
      </label>
    </div>
    <div>
      <label class="checkbox">
        <input type="checkbox" name="agree">
        I agree to the <a href="#">terms and conditions</a>
      </label>
    </div>
  </p>
</div>
<% end %>


